{
  "stem": "1677.1",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had charred chocolate and a cake, and I got presents.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You can imagine during the war what I would get-- a fountain pen, maybe, or whatever.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we had one bar mitzvah, Fred Parker who is here Pulitzer.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I so remember he was singing so nicely in that synagogue, and suddenly there was [NON-ENGLISH], which I never was allowed to go.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I envied.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The And my father made white flag with a blue Magen David.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I did not realize what it meant.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And everybody was having flags.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I was marching with what today is the flag of the state of Israel.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And it is many, many years ago.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And the ladies upstairs were throwing lollies down.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "My mother told me, I forbid you to touch one lolly.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "You have a shop full of lollies.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I donated a crate of lollies.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "If you pick up one lolly, I beat you up.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And then suddenly, everybody started to scramble for the lollies.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "So I scrambled more than everybody else.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I couldn't resist the temptation.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "All these lollies, and I am not allowed.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I was forever in the rebellion.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That started, unfortunately, and there was no one to control it, because when I think that my parents realized that I have no future in this Jewish school-- the teacher was taken away, the other children they are all deported-- I was there on my own with one girl.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She died of cancer last year in Israel.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "When did the deportations begin?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "1940.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So my mother was worried about me, and in '42, when it was really very tough, they had connections, and it cost an awful lot of money-- they sent me to a Catholic convent of the Pauvre Soeur de Notre Dame.",
      "word_count": 41
    }
  ],
